posts.text:
トピずれだけどさ、松坂桃李と濱田岳の役反対でもよかったかなと思う。
あんなに抜け作で頼りない旦那なら顔二枚目の人使わない方がよかった。
それに濱田岳の方がもっと破天荒にクズ旦那を演じてくれたような。
だけど旦那の真の姿を信じて付いていくてん、そしててんを見守る高橋一生と松坂桃李。
実らない想いだけど、二枚目イケメンの二人が陰ながらてんを支えるって筋書きの方がグッとくるわ。
これずっと言いたかったの。長々とすまぬ。

原标题：东风主导研发全球首台自动驾驶电动公交，本月底在特定区运营
图为全球首辆自动驾驶电动公交在道路测试中。楚天金报 图 昨日，湖北省经信委发布消息，由东风襄阳旅行车有限公司和北京理工大学联合研发的全球首辆6.7米自动驾驶纯电动城市公交车，成功完成厂内测试。两台样车已发往深圳市，做最后的实况路线测试，预计11月底将在特定区域正式运营。
这辆自动驾驶公交车集自动控制、体系结构、人工智能、视觉计算等众多技术于一体，配有激光雷达、毫米波雷达、摄像机、GPS天线及车载工控机感知收集周围环境，通过工控机、整车控制器及can网络对路况环境分析，做出制动、转向、驻车、灯光、开关车门等指令，能够对其他道路使用者和突发状况做出反应。

posts.text:
Originally Posted by klaps_05 TLDR : The more you discuss what could be changed in vanilla, the higher the chances are something will and you end up with LFR, 4k graphics and ElvUI. (listed these things as things which did not exist in vanilla, not that they are bad).
I find it quite interesting there are so many threads on this forum discussing possible vanilla changes. I have been playing since vanilla and still do every expansion. I love retail, I appreciate WoW's past. I have nothing against bring WoW: Classic - the more content there is for people the better.
However, if the goal is to preserve the authentic vanilla experience, outside of bug/crash fixes, nothing else changes. From classes to bosses to drops to systems - everything remains as in vanilla. If you attempt to discuss changes, authentic goes out the door. The only QoL changes must be bug fixes and nothing else.
Just have a look at the list of threads/polls now on this page:
"Poll: Vanilla WoW Yay or Nah to the new graphics?"
22% want new graphics
"Poll: What changes to classic would you be okay with?"
35 % want modern addon/lua/macro support
34 % want modern character models/animations
34 % want modern graphics
32 % want modern interface
15% want nerf to known gold farming spots
20 % want class balancing
22 % want spec viability
38 % want auto loot as an option
30 % want auto area loot
13% want quest helper
9% want premade dungeon finder
26 % want stacking soulshards
22 % want debuffs raised/removed
12% want limit stacking of consumables
17% want more challenging bosses
17% want guild bank
37% want no changes
"QoL needed for an amazing classic experience"
"Poll: Should Talents be Class-Specific rather than Spec-specific?"
"A change classic servers absolutely needs"
"Poll: Would you prefer no updates or updates?"
"Why WoW: Classic Needs the Tweaks"
Now, sure, some of these threads are clearly trolls and bait, but you realize Blizzard will poll the COMMUNITY . That means EVERYONE, people who love Classic AND people who HATE classic will vote. People who have never played Classic will vote for features they never experienced first hand.
While the Classic community is quite vocal and has been asking for Classic for a long time, the casual WoW retail players are a lot more. So how would you select whose votes matter?
This question is really important when it comes down to the intricate details of vanilla, such as the detailed poll I posted above in this post illustrates - stacking soulshards? debuff slots? spec viability? You can see a basic poll on mmochampion results in such high %s for things which are unthinkable for vanilla. Make polls only for the people that have accounts in classic. Problem solved
If blizzard make polls they're gonna be in game and away from the haters.

University of Michigan Broadcast Producer Inter in Ann Arbor , Michigan 
Job Summary 
Michigan Radio, the public radio stations of the University of Michigan, is seeking a creative podcast trainer/producer to work on our Detroit Journalism Cooperative project. The individual will work with Michigan Radio to identify interested community members in the MorningSide neighborhood, and assist them in the creation and production of a hyper-local neighborhood news and community affairs podcast. 
This is a one-year term limited appointment with benefits -January 2018 through December 2018. 
Responsibilities* 
Main duties include: 
Identifying, training and working with interested MorningSide neighborhood residents and community leaders to record and produce interviews, features and other audio for monthly podcast. 
Editing multiple complex interviews and features on deadline. 
Work with marketing department to promote and distribute podcast within neighborhood. 
Develop and implement coverage ideas for the podcast. 
Additional duties may include: 
Reproducing podcast material for air on Michigan Radio and Detroit Journalism Cooperative (DJC) partners or posting on website. 
Creates creative concepts and copy for promotion and outreach for program. 
Maintains the podcast's social media presence in conjunction with the station's online team. 
Paricipate in weekly DJC editorial meetings. 
Participate in audience engagement activities as developed by Michigan Radio and/or the DJC. 
Other duties as assigned. 
Required Qualifications* 
The candidate must be self-motivated, an organized producer and have experience in broadcast production. Bachelor's degree in journalism, communications, or related field or equivalent of experience and knowledge; 1-3 years recent experience producing audio content, outstanding radio production skills; complete proficiency with fast turnaround digital audio editing; ability to work with and train diverse members of a community; demonstrated ability to poroduce high-quality work on deadline and handle several projects at once; strong editorial judgement; and ability to work with a variety of personality types in a team environment. Must be able to demonstrate an understanding of public radio's core values. 
Familiarity with Audition, Content Depot, and Newsboss a plus. 
Additional Information 
Audio of recent interview production work must be submitted with application. Please send mp3 or links to zoeclark@umich.edu; vduffy@umich.edu; sarahhu@umich.edu

posts.text: Houzz тур: Сказочная квартира в духе Кевина Слоана Мистический реализм — интерьер с лавандовыми стенами и зеленой кухней Светлана Лянгасова 7 ноября, 2017 Постоянный автор Houzz, журналист. Обладатель двух премий «Признание» и множества именных грамот за победы в журналистских конкурсах, организованных госструктурами. В интерьере ценю функциональность. Считаю, что форма и цвет должны привносить в обстановку не только индивидуальность, но и уют. Постоянный автор Houzz, журналист. Обладатель двух премий «Признание» и множества... Еще E-mail Размер: 175 кв.м; высота потолка — 3 м Кто здесь живет: семья из четырех человек. Дочери 16 лет, сыну — 5 Фото: Александр Шевцов «В момент работы над проектом я была увлечена полотнами художников мистического реализма » , — вспоминает Виктория Лазарева. Продумывая концепцию, дизайнер показала хозяйке работы американского художника Кевина Слоана. Заказчице очень понравились его аллегории. Так в гостиной появились пеликаны — копии работ этого художника, а на лоджии — трогательный кролик. Художник из Вильнюса изготовил для этого интерьера зеркальные панно с райскими птицами, а калининградский скульптор — загадочные листья из латуни. «Все-таки сказка — это то, чего нам не хватает во взрослой жизни », — отмечает Виктория. Светлана Лянгасова Прожив в этой квартире 12 лет, супруги решили сделать ремонт и пригласили дизайнера. « Я сразу оценила планировку: большой холл, комнаты правильной формы, большие окна и высоту потолка 3 м » , —вспоминает автор проекта. Спальни и ванная комнаты расположены в дальней части квартиры и отделены от общих зон коридором. Достойная планировка не требовала серьезных изменений и отвечала потребностям заказчиков. Светлана Лянгасова План квартиры В итоге планировка осталась практически в исходном виде. Единственное, строители убрали остекление между лоджиями и примыкающими к ним комнатами. Благодаря этому в комнате дочери появился «кабинет» для занятий, а рядом с кухней — зона отдыха. Увеличилась и площадь спальни. Светлана Лянгасова На фото: столик Eicthholz; на стене — копии полотен американского художника Кевина Слоана Журнальный столик для гостиной искали долго. Только когда на стены смонтировали пальмовые ветви из латуни, Виктория поняла, что стол с аналогичным латунным основанием и тонированной стеклянной столешницей — то, что требуется. Светлана Лянгасова На фото: обои Sanderson; кухня Aster Cucine, Avenue Факт: Обои для кухни и всей квартиры выбрали за час. Ботанический рисунок на кухонных обоях рифмуется с гарнитуром сложного оттенка зеленого. Светлана Лянгасова На фото: обои Cole & Son; на стене — копия полотна Кевина Слоана Для зоны отдыха на бывшей лоджии Виктория выбрала о бои из коллекции Whimsical ( « Причудливый » ) . Их рисунок задает настроение, продолжая сюжет картины с кроликом. Светлана Лянгасова На фото: обои с цветочным орнаментом Sanderson « Строгий дизайн мебели, отсутствие тюля на окнах, чтобы с самого утра впустить солнце; элегантные обои и снова искусство — копия картины Э. Мане “Флейтист”. Для спальни мы выбрали мотивы, отражающие вкусы владелицы » , — рассказывает Виктория. Светлана Лянгасова Заказчики хотели после ремонта вернуться в яркую и необычную квартиру. Поэтому главным инструментом дизайнера стал цвет. «Все и нтерьеры разные, как и их владельцы. И чем интереснее заказчик, тем интереснее получается интерьер » , — подчеркивает Виктория. Чтобы раскрыть личность человека и узнать, в каком доме он хочет жить, дизайнер проводит настоящее исследование. Виктория показывает заказчикам образы готовых интерьеров, материалы (от керамики до тканей), изучает вкусы хозяев через восприятие ими фактур, примеров цветовых сочетаний.

Beauty lies in the eye of the beholder. 
Apart from beauty, the eyes speak too!!  When one is crying anyone can see openly!!  When one is sad the eyes reveal!  When one is angry the eyes say so!  When one is happy the eyes express it! 
The eyes even  reveal when one is not well or even when drunk!!  The eyes seldom hide the true feelings of a human being. 
Babies respond more positively to attractive eyes and faces.  Grown-ups, when considering a romantic partner, some have an eye color preference. However, it may not be the color that is so attractive, but the limbal ring that encircles the iris or colored part of the eye. 

In many the limbal ring  is most noticeable in light colored eyes, such as blue, green or hazel. The opacity of this ring fluctuates in the eye and without realizing it, this could be used as an indicator of how healthy a person is and therefore, how attractive that person is. 
The face is a picture of the mind as the eyes are its interpreter. When one pays attention, the eyes provide a lot of information about the emotional state of the person across: 

When one is worried, the eye-brows furrow, making the eyes look smaller. When one is happy, the eyebrows raise unconsciously, making them appear larger and sparkle giving a "bright-eyed" appearance. Talking about artistes, they have often spoken through their eyes, be it: The romance of Rajesh Khanna or Emran Hashmi; The anger of Amitabh Bachchan or Sunny Deol; The sadness of Charlie Chaplin or Dilip Kumar;  The strictness of Adolf Hitler or Amrish Puri; The beauty of Marilyn Monroe or Aishwarya Rai, and The seductiveness of Rekha, etc. etc. The eyes are not only the window to one's soul, but also a mirror which reflect human health. TEKNOLOJİDE KADINLARIN ZAMANI Tece ve Davultepe Mahalleleri Berdan içme suyuna kavuştu Mersin Büyükşehir Belediyesi Mersin Su ve Kanalizasyon İdaresi (MESKİ) Genel Müdürlüğü’nün çalışmaları sonucu merkez Mezitli ilçesinin Tece ve Davultepe Mahalleleri yıllar sonra Berdan içme suyuna kavuştu.MESKİ Genel Müdürlüğü,... 07 Kasım 2017 Salı 10:56   @BursaHaberMedya 
Mersin Büyükşehir Belediyesi Mersin Su ve Kanalizasyon İdaresi (MESKİ) Genel Müdürlüğü’nün çalışmaları sonucu merkez Mezitli ilçesinin Tece ve Davultepe Mahalleleri yıllar sonra Berdan içme suyuna kavuştu. 
MESKİ Genel Müdürlüğü, yaklaşık 30 bin nüfusa sahip Tece ve Davultepe Mahallelerinde içme suyu isale hattı çalışmalarını tamamladı. Muhtelif çaplarda 11 bin 550 metrelik içme suyu isale hattının tamamlanmasıyla Berdan içme suyu Tece ve Davultepe Mahallelerine ulaştı. 
Çalışmalara ilişkin açıklama yapan Mersin Büyükşehir Belediye Başkanı Burhanettin Kocamaz, Mersin genelinde içme suyu olmayan ve su sorunu olan mahallelerde çalışmaların aralıksız devam ettiğini belirtti. Mezitli’nin Tece ve Davultepe Mahallelerine 3 milyon TL’lik yatırımla 11 bin 550 metre uzunluğunda içme suyu isale hattı çalışmasını tamamladıklarını ifade eden Kocamaz, Mersin’de su sorunu kalmaması için çalışmaların süreceğini kaydetti. Kocamaz, “Tüm ilçelerimizde olduğu gibi Mezitli ilçemizde de altyapı ve içme suyu problemleri çözülene kadar projelerimize devam edeceğiz. Son çalışmamızla Mezitli ilçemizde Tece ve Davultepe Mahallelerimizde yaşayan vatandaşlarımızın içme suyu sorununu yeni içme suyu isale hattı çalışmalarını tamamlayarak çözüme kavuşturduk. Hayırlı ve uğurlu olsun. Mersin Büyükşehir Belediyesi olarak vatandaşlarımızın temiz ve sağlıklı içme suyuna ulaşabilmesi için çalışmalarımıza ara vermeden devam ediyoruz” dedi. 
Tece Mahallesi Muhtarı Hilmi Kara ise içme sularının Dedekavak su kaynağından temin edildiğini belirterek, nüfusun hızla artmasıyla suların yetersiz geldiğini söyledi. Kara, “Yıllardır Berdan içme suyunun gelmesini bekledik. Başkanımız Burhanettin Kocamaz’ın sayesinde suyumuza kavuştuk. Emeği geçenlerden Allah razı olsun. Mersin Büyükşehir Belediyesi vatandaşlarımıza büyük hizmetler veriyor” diye konuştu. 
Tece Deniz Mahallesi Muhtarı Aziz Aydoğdu da Berdan içme suyunun mahalle sakinleri tarafından sevinçle karşılandığını dile getirerek, “Berdan içme suyu ile mahallemize gelen su miktarı ve içme suyu kalitesi arttı. Mutluğumuzun tarifi olamaz” şeklinde konuştu. Davultepe 75. Yıl Mahallesi Muhtarı Yaşar Aytekin ise “Davultepe’de artezyen kuyusundan içme suyu içiyorduk. Artık Berdan içme suyunu içeceğiz. Çok büyük sıkıntılar çektik. Burhanettin Kocamaz Başkanımız sayesinde bu sıkıntılarımız ortadan kalktı. Artık çeşmelerimizden su akıyor. Burhanettin Kocamaz’a ve emeği geçen MESKİ yetkililerine teşekkür ediyorum” ifadelerini kullandı. 1

posts.text:
Beginnen met Rust, de taal voor veiliger code Duik er gewoon in! Overweeg je Rust? Hier bespreken we hoe je met de tool chain begint, hoe je projecten opzet, hoe je werkt met code van anderen en hoe je bibliotheken beheert. Beginnen met Rust, de taal voor veiliger code Overweeg je Rust? Hier bespreken we hoe je met de tool chain begint, hoe je projecten opzet, hoe je werkt met code van anderen en hoe je bibliotheken beheert. 0 Reacties Bewaren 
Over the last couple of years, Rust has gone from a curiosity brewed up in the lab of a Mozilla employee to a strong contender for writing the next generation of native apps and bare-metal solutions. But those advances come from Rust providing its own tool chain and component management system - along with its own features and quirks. 
This article walks through the basics of setting up a working environment in Rust, configuring an IDE, and making the most of the tool set Rust provides for app development. The basics of the Rust development environment 
Rust's tool chain consists primarily of the Rust compiler, rustc , along with tools for managing a Rust installation. Because Rust is under constant development, the Rust tool chain is designed to be easy to keep up to date. 
Software projects are often provided via multiple channels, to separate the stable and beta versions of the code. Rust's tool chain works the same way, offering three channels for its tool chain: 
Stable: Major point releases, which emerge every six weeks or so. 
Beta: Candidates for the next major point release, which emerge more often. 
Nightly: The most immediate build, with access to cutting-edge features but no guarantees as to their stability. 
As developer Karol Kuczmarski has pointed out , it's best to think of the nightly Rust channel as its own language. Some Rust features are only available in the nightly channel, and they can only be activated by special compiler directives. In other words, they won't even compile on the beta or stable channels. That's by design, because there's no guarantee the nightly features will be supported anywhere else. 
In short: 
Use stable for actual production work. 
Use beta to test current software against upcoming versions to see if anything may break in the upgrade. 
Only use nightly for sandboxed experiments with Rust's newest features. Choose a platform to develop in Rust 
Rust supports all three major platforms —Windows, Linux, and MacOS—in both 32- and 64-bit incarnations, with official binaries for each. A slew of other platforms also have official binaries, but they don't have the same level of automated testing coverage. These second-class platforms include ARMv6 and ARMv7 for iOS, Android, and Linux; MIPS Linux and MIPS64 Linux; and WebAssembly . Other platforms, like Solaris or Illumos, are supported through unofficial builds. 
Rust's development team has stated that it isn't one of Rust's missions to be as broadly portable as possible. For example, although Rust is available on many ARM architectures, it isn't guaranteed that Rust will be officially supported on low-end hardware platforms. 
That said, there should be a supported Rust build available for the vast majority of common, mainstream use cases—namely, 32- and 64-bit Windows, Linux, and MacOS. 
If you're planning to develop in Rust on Windows , keep your tool chains in mind. Rust supports two tool chains on Windows: 
the native Microsoft Visual C (MSVC) ABI 
the GNU ABI used by the GCC linker. 
Because almost all C/C++ software built in Windows uses MSVC anyway, you'll want to use the MSVC tool chain the vast majority of the time. If you ever need GCC, it'll most likely be for interoperating with third-party libraries built in Windows with GCC. 
The good news is that Rust's tool chain management system lets you keep both MSVC and GCC tool chains installed, and it lets you switch between them on a project-by-project basis. 
One of Rust's compilation targets is WebAssembly, meaning you can write in Rust and deploy to a web browser. WebAssembly itself is still rough around the edges, and so is Rust's support for it. But if you're ambitious and want to get your hands messy, a project called Wargo can simplify the compilation process. (Note: Node.js is required.)
